jroutine-androidchannel 6.0.0

Parallel programming on the go.

See: Description

Packages 
Package Description
com.github.dm.jrt.android.channel
Utility classes handling routine channels specific to the Android platform.
com.github.dm.jrt.android.v11.channel
Utility classes handling routine channels with support for Android sparse array collections.
com.github.dm.jrt.android.v4.channel
Utility classes handling routine channels with support for Android sparse array collections included in the compatibility library.
Parallel programming on the go.

Android customization of channel utility classes based on the jroutine-channel library.

Usage examples

Example 1: blending the output of two channels. 
    
      final OutputChannel<Object> channel = AndroidChannels.blend(channel1, channel2).buildChannels();
Example 2: concatenating the output of two channels. 
    
      final OutputChannel<Object> channel = SparseChannels.concat(channel1, channel2).buildChannels();
Example 3: joining the output of two channels. 
    
      final OutputChannel<List<Object>> channel = SparseChannelsCompat.join(channel1, channel2).buildChannels();
